VisualizationCSV
VisualizationCSV.java
Transforms/Converts a methodResult into a CSV String as used in the US (Separators: "," and "\n")
- Values of the same column are separated by a ","
- Rows are separated by a "\n"
- The first row contains the column names
- The second row contains the column data type (as number) as defined in Types (sql)

VisualizationHTMLTable
VisualizationHTMLTable.java
Transforms/Converts a methodResult into a HTML Table (or HTML List if there is only one column in the row list) Warning: The HTML table/list does not contain/list the datatypes of the cells/columns!
- Simple HTML-Table with a small border
- The first row contains the column names
- There is no denotation of the columns' datatypes

VisualizationXML
VisualizationXML.java
Transforms/Converts a method result into an XML-String, where each row is stored as String-Array (using a subset of the syntax/semantic the LAS-HTTP-Connector)
Data Format:
- XML with the same (/subset of the) syntax/semantic as used by the HTTP-LAS-Connector
- Each row is stored as String array parameters element
- The first row contains the column names
- The second row denotes the data type of the column as String as used in Java, e.g.
